Hillview Capital Advisors, LLC Buys Red Hat Inc, Vanguard Total Stock Market, Sells Apple Inc, Ares Capital CorpJuly 27, 2017 |  About: 
VTI  +0%
RHT  +0%
AAPL  +0%
ARCC  +0% 



Wayne, PA, based Investment company Hillview Capital Advisors, LLC buys Red Hat Inc, Vanguard Total Stock Market, sells Apple Inc, Ares Capital Corp during the 3-months ended 2017-06-30, according to the most recent filings of the investment company, Hillview Capital Advisors, LLC. As of 2017-06-30, Hillview Capital Advisors, LLC owns 5 stocks with a total value of $22 million.  These are the details of the buys and sells.New Purchases: RHT, Added Positions: VTI, Reduced Positions: VEA, VT, Sold Out: AAPL, ARCC, For the details of Hillview Capital Advisors, LLC's stock buys and sells, go to http://www.gurufocus.com/StockBuy.php?GuruName=Hillview+Capital+Advisors%2C+LLCThese are the top 5 holdings of Hillview Capital Advisors, LLCVanguard FTSE Developed Markets (VEA) - 358,778 shares, 66.52% of the total portfolio.  Shares reduced by 5.65%Vanguard Total World Stock Index (VT) - 89,806 shares, 27.4% of the total portfolio.  Shares reduced by 9.98%Vanguard Total Stock Market (VTI) - 4,095 shares, 2.29% of the total portfolio.  Shares added by 73.59%Tortoise Energy Infrastructure Corporation (TYG) - 16,420 shares, 2.24% of the total portfolio. Red Hat Inc (RHT) - 3,600 shares, 1.55% of the total portfolio.  New PositionNew Purchase: Red Hat Inc (RHT)
VTI 30-Year Financial DataThe intrinsic value of VTIPeter Lynch Chart of VTIHillview Capital Advisors, LLC initiated holdings in  Red Hat Inc.  The purchase prices were between $84.68 and $99.42, with an estimated average price of $89.09.   The stock is now traded at around $98.70. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 1.55%. The holdings were 3,600 shares as of 2017-06-30. Added: Vanguard Total Stock Market (VTI)Hillview Capital Advisors, LLC added to the holdings in  Vanguard Total Stock Market by 73.59%.  The purchase prices were between $119.55 and $126.27, with an estimated average price of $123.16.   The stock is now traded at around $126.56. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.97%. The holdings were 4,095 shares as of 2017-06-30. Sold Out: Apple Inc (AAPL)Hillview Capital Advisors, LLC sold out the holdings in  Apple Inc.  The sale prices were between $140.68 and $156.1, with an estimated average price of $147.76. Sold Out: Ares Capital Corp (ARCC)Hillview Capital Advisors, LLC sold out the holdings in  Ares Capital Corp.  The sale prices were between $16.18 and $17.64, with an estimated average price of $16.87. Here is the complete portfolio of Hillview Capital Advisors, LLC. Also check out:
