Mr. Hochberg is a member of the Board of Trustees and serves as Chairman of the Investment Committee of The Jewish Home and Hospital Lifecare System. He is a member of the Board of Directors of the Jewish Institute for National Security Affairs (JINSA) and the Federal Enforcement Homeland Security Foundation. He serves on the Board of Advisors of the George Washington University School of Business and Fuel for Truth. He is a member of U.J.A. Federation's Investment Advisors Division, Variety - The Children's Charity Wall Street Division.
Mr. Hochberg holds an M.B.A. in Finance from The Leonard N. Stern School of Business at New York University and a B.B.A. in Accounting from The George Washington University.
